{
	"name": "King’s Candle",
	"type": "object",
	"img": "icons/consumables/vegetable/root-alien-green.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>King’s Candle is often found near cliffs and quarries, for it thrives on sunny slopes and rocky ground. A striking, tall plant with soft, silvery-green leaves, King’s Candle has bright yellow flowers and a thick central stalk up to five feet tall. The flowers are known for their numbing capabilities when crushed and mixed with water or wine. This mixture can be applied to wounds to relieve pain and encourage healing.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Effect. </strong></em>Applying the King’s Candle mixture grants 1d6 temporary hit points, which last until the end of the creature’s next short or long rest.</p>",
